SIMPLE: di
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Di-
<hw>Di-</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[Gr. <grk>di`s-</grk> twice; akin to <?/
two, L. <ets>bis</ets> twice. See <er>Two</er>, and cf. <er>Bi-</er>,
<er>Dia-</er>. The L. pref. <ets>dis-</ets> sometimes assumes the form
<ets>di</ets>-. See <er>Dis-</er>.]</ety> <def>A prefix, signifying
<sig>twofold</sig>, <sig>double</sig>, <sig>twice</sig></def>;
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>denoting <sig>two</sig> atoms, radicals, groups,
or equivalents, as the case may be. See <er>Bi-</er>, 2.</def></p>

<p><ent>Di-</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Dia-</ent>⟦br⟧
<mhw>{

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Di-
<hw>Di-</hw> }</mhw>. <ety>[Gr.
<grk>dia`</grk> through; orig., dividing into two parts; akin to <?/
two. See <er>Two</er>, and cf. 1st <er>Di-</er>.]</ety> <def>A prefix
denoting <sig>through</sig>; also, <sig>between</sig>, <sig>apart</sig>,
<sig>asunder</sig>, <sig>across</sig>. Before a vowel <ex>dia-</ex>
becomes <altname>di-</altname>; <as>as, <ex>di</ex>actinic;
<ex>di</ex>electric, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Diabase</ent>⟦br⟧
